  "prompt": "What is the best comedy movie ever?",
  "response": "The \"best\" comedy movie is subjective and depends on individual tastes. However, one widely acclaimed comedy film is \"Monty Python and the Holy Grail\" (1975). Directed by Terry Gilliam and Terry Jones, this British comedy has gained a cult following for its absurd humor, memorable quotes, and iconic scenes. It follows King Arthur and his knights on a quest for the Holy Grail, encountering various humorous challenges along the way.\n\nOther notable comedy films often mentioned among the best include:\n\n1. **\"Airplane!\" (1980)** - A classic spoof of disaster films, known for its rapid-fire jokes and slapstick humor.\n2. **\"The Big Lebowski\" (1998)** - A Coen Brothers film that has become a cult classic, known for its quirky characters and offbeat humor.\n3. **\"Some Like It Hot\" (1959)** - A brilliant comedy directed by Billy Wilder, featuring unforgettable performances by Marilyn Monroe, Tony Curtis, and Jack Lemmon.\n4. **\"Blazing Saddles\" (1974)** - Mel Brooks' hilarious and irreverent take on Western films, filled with satire and slapstick.\n\nUltimately, the best comedy movie for you would be the one that aligns with your sense of humor and leaves you laughing the most.",
